    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This potent technique encourages the feral instinct of man and beast alike, requiring them to succeed at a save or be overcome by bloodlust and attack their nearest enemy without regard for their own safety. If no enemies are nearby, they will attack the nearest creature instead. The subject(s) continue attacking until the object of their rage is dead or this technique's duration expires.<br><br>Subjects also receive a +2 enhancement bonus to Strength and Dexterity, a +2 morale bonus to Will saves, and become unable to use spells, powers, spelllike abilities or techniques, as well as any Charisma-, Dexterity- and Intelligence-based skills (except Balance, Escape Artist, Intimidate and Ride), as well as being unable to use the Chakra Control and Concentration skills, or actions requiring patience or concentrations. Creatures with an Intelligence of 3 or less do not get a save to resist the technique.</p>\n\n\n\n",
